wlsxIfExtMIB.name: wlsxIfExtMIB

revisions.description: Deprecated wlsxIfExtPortTable and added new table wlsxIfExtNPortTable

wlsxIfExtMIB.contactinfo: Postal: 1322 Crossman Avenue Sunnyvale, CA 94089 E-mail: dl-support@arubanetworks.com Phone: +1 408 227 4500
wlsxIfExtMIB.description: This MIB module defines MIB objects which provide System level information about the Aruba controller.

wlsxIfExtPortTable.name: wlsxIfExtPortTable
wlsxIfExtPortTable.description: The table of processors contained by the controller. This table is deprecated in favor of wlsxIfExtNPortTable.

wlsxIfExtPortEntry.name: wlsxIfExtPortEntry
wlsxIfExtPortEntry.description: An entry for one processor contained by the controller.

ifExtSlotNumber.name: ifExtSlotNumber
ifExtSlotNumber.description: This object represents the Physical Slot of the Interface.

ifExtPortNumber.name: ifExtPortNumber
ifExtPortNumber.description: This object represents the Physical Port of the Interface.

ifExtPortIfIndex.name: ifExtPortIfIndex
ifExtPortIfIndex.description: This is the ifIndex in ifTable, representing this slot and port. This object is deprecated in favour of ifExtNPortIfIndex.

ifExtAdminState.name: ifExtAdminState
ifExtAdminState.description: The desired state of the interface. This object is deprecated in favour of ifExtNAdminState.

ifExtOperState.name: ifExtOperState
ifExtOperState.description: The current operational state of the interface. This object is deprecated in favour of ifExtNOperState.

ifExtPoeState.name: ifExtPoeState
ifExtPoeState.description: The current state of the power over ethernet capability of the port. This object is deprecated in favour of ifExtNPoeState.

ifExtIsTrusted.name: ifExtIsTrusted
ifExtIsTrusted.description: The object indicates if the port is used in the trusted side of the network or the untrusted side. This object is deprecated in favour of ifExtNIsTrusted.

ifExtDot1DState.name: ifExtDot1DState
ifExtDot1DState.description: Current Dot1d state of the Port. This object provides default switch port value if ifExtIsMonitoring is true(1). This object is deprecated in favour of ifExtNDot1DState.

ifExtMode.name: ifExtMode
ifExtMode.description: This object indicates if the port is in a Trunk mode or access mode. This object provides default switch port value if ifExtIsMonitoring is true(1). This object is deprecated in favour of ifExtNMode.

ifExtAccessVlanId.name: ifExtAccessVlanId
ifExtAccessVlanId.description: The VLAN Id when the port is in Access Mode. This object provides default switch port value if ifExtIsMonitoring is true(1). This object is deprecated in favour of ifExtNAccessVlanId.

ifExtTrunkNativeVlanId.name: ifExtTrunkNativeVlanId
ifExtTrunkNativeVlanId.description: The native VLAN Id of the Port, when the port is in dot1q mode. This object provides default switch port value if ifExtIsMonitoring is true(1). This object is deprecated in favour of ifExtNTrunkNativeVlanId.

ifExtTrunkIsAllowedAll.name: ifExtTrunkIsAllowedAll
ifExtTrunkIsAllowedAll.description: When the mode of the port is Trunk, this Object indicates if the port is part of all the configured Vlans. This object provides default switch port value if ifExtIsMonitoring is true(1). This object is deprecated in favour of ifExtNTrunkIsAllowedAll.

ifExtTrunkAllowedVlanList.name: ifExtTrunkAllowedVlanList
ifExtTrunkAllowedVlanList.description: A string of octets containing one bit per VLAN for a total of 4096 VLANs in the management domain. The most significant bit of the octet string is the lowest value VLAN of 4096 VLANs. By setting the bit(1) we indicate that the vlan is part of the interface. The most significant bit of the bitmap is transmitted first. Note that if the length of this string is less than 512 octets, any 'missing' octets are assumed to contain the value zero. This object provides default switch port value if ifExtIsMonitoring is true(1). This object is deprecated in favour of ifExtNTrunkAllowedVlanList.

ifExtIngressACLName.name: ifExtIngressACLName
ifExtIngressACLName.description: This object represents the Ingress ACL name applied to the port. An Empty string indicates that there is not ACL applied on this port. This object is deprecated in favour of ifExtNIngressACLName.

ifExtEgressACLName.name: ifExtEgressACLName
ifExtEgressACLName.description: This object represents the Egress ACL name applied to the port. An Empty string indicates that there is not ACL applied on this port. This object is deprecated in favour of ifExtNEgressACLName.

ifExtSessionACLName.name: ifExtSessionACLName
ifExtSessionACLName.description: This object represents the Session ACL name applied to the port. An Empty string indicates that there is not ACL applied on this port. This object is deprecated in favour of ifExtNEgressACLName.

ifExtXsecVlan.name: ifExtXsecVlan
ifExtXsecVlan.description: This object indicates if the port is an Xsec Port. This object is deprecated in favour of ifExtNXsecVlan.

ifExtIsMonitoring.name: ifExtIsMonitoring
ifExtIsMonitoring.description: This object indicates if the port is used for Port monitoring. When the value of this object is true(1), then below objects provide default switch port values configured on this port. ifExtMode, ifExtAccessVlanId, ifExtTrunkNativeVlanId, ifExtTrunkIsAllowedAll, ifExtTrunkAllowedVlanList This object is deprecated in favour of ifExtNIsMonitoring.

ifExtIsMux.name: ifExtIsMux
ifExtIsMux.description: This object indicates if the port is used as a MUX Port. This object is deprecated in favour of ifExtNIsMux.

ifExtPortSpeed.name: ifExtPortSpeed
ifExtPortSpeed.description: Speed of the Port. This object is deprecated in favour of ifExtNPortSpeed.

ifExtPortDuplex.name: ifExtPortDuplex
ifExtPortDuplex.description: Duplexity of the Port. This object is deprecated in favour of ifExtNPortDuplex.

ifExtPortType.name: ifExtPortType
ifExtPortType.description: Type of the Port. This object is deprecated in favour of ifExtNPortType.

ifExtDescr.name: ifExtDescr
ifExtDescr.description: Port Description. This object is deprecated in favour of ifExtNDescr.

wlsxIfExtVlanEntry.description: An entry for one processor contained by the controller.

ifExtVlanId.name: ifExtVlanId

ifExtVlanStatus.name: ifExtVlanStatus

ifExtVlanMemberStatus.description: A Row status Object used to create/modify and indicate the status row.

ifExtVlanMemberSlot.name: ifExtVlanMemberSlot
ifExtVlanMemberSlot.description: The slot index of the slot referred to by this row (1-based).

ifExtVlanMemberPort.name: ifExtVlanMemberPort
ifExtVlanMemberPort.description: The slot index of the slot referred to by this row (1-based).

wlsxIfExtVlanInterfaceEntry.name: wlsxIfExtVlanInterfaceEntry
wlsxIfExtVlanInterfaceEntry.description: An entry for one processor contained by the controller.

ifExtVlanInterfaceIfIndex.name: ifExtVlanInterfaceIfIndex
ifExtVlanInterfaceIfIndex.description: This is the ifIndex in ifTable, representing VLAN Interface.

ifExtVlanInterfaceDescription.name: ifExtVlanInterfaceDescription
ifExtVlanInterfaceDescription.description: This Object indicates the description of the Interface.

ifExtVlanInterfaceBWContract.name: ifExtVlanInterfaceBWContract
ifExtVlanInterfaceBWContract.description: This Object indicates the Bandwidth contract on the interface.

ifExtVlanInterfaceAdminState.name: ifExtVlanInterfaceAdminState
ifExtVlanInterfaceAdminState.description: This Object indicates the administrative state of the Interface.

ifExtVlanInterfaceOperState.name: ifExtVlanInterfaceOperState
ifExtVlanInterfaceOperState.description: This Object indicates the operational state of the Interface.

ifExtVlanInterfaceIpAddress.name: ifExtVlanInterfaceIpAddress
ifExtVlanInterfaceIpAddress.description: This Object indicates the IP Address of the Interface.

ifExtVlanInterfaceIpMask.name: ifExtVlanInterfaceIpMask
ifExtVlanInterfaceIpMask.description: This Object indicates the subnet mask of the Interface.

ifExtVlanInterfaceIsLocalArp.name: ifExtVlanInterfaceIsLocalArp
ifExtVlanInterfaceIsLocalArp.description: This Object indicates if the Local Arp is set on the Interface.

ifExtVlanInterfaceStatus.name: ifExtVlanInterfaceStatus
ifExtVlanInterfaceStatus.description: A Row status Object used to create/modify and indicate the status row.

ifExtVlanInterfaceIpRouting.name: ifExtVlanInterfaceIpRouting
ifExtVlanInterfaceIpRouting.description: This Object indicates if the IP routing is set on the Interface.

ifExtVlanInterfaceIpNatInside.name: ifExtVlanInterfaceIpNatInside
ifExtVlanInterfaceIpNatInside.description: This Object indicates if the IP nat inside is set on the Interface.

ifExtVlanInterfaceIpIgmpSnooping.name: ifExtVlanInterfaceIpIgmpSnooping
ifExtVlanInterfaceIpIgmpSnooping.description: This Object indicates if the IP IGMP snooping is set on the Interface.

ifExtNSlotNumber.name: ifExtNSlotNumber
ifExtNSlotNumber.description: This object represents the user-visible (zero-based) Physical Slot of the Interface.

ifExtNModuleNumber.name: ifExtNModuleNumber
ifExtNModuleNumber.description: This object represents the user-visible (zero-based) Physical Module of the Interface.

ifExtNPortNumber.name: ifExtNPortNumber
ifExtNPortNumber.description: This object represents the user-visible (zero-based) Physical Port of the Interface.

ifExtNPortIfIndex.name: ifExtNPortIfIndex
ifExtNPortIfIndex.description: This is the ifIndex in ifTable, representing this slot, module and port.

ifExtNAdminState.name: ifExtNAdminState
ifExtNAdminState.description: The desired state of the interface.

ifExtNOperState.name: ifExtNOperState
ifExtNOperState.description: The current operational state of the interface.

ifExtNPoeState.name: ifExtNPoeState
ifExtNPoeState.description: The current state of the power over ethernet capability of the port.

ifExtNIsTrusted.name: ifExtNIsTrusted
ifExtNIsTrusted.description: The object indicates if the port is used in the trusted side of the network or the untrusted side.

ifExtNDot1DState.name: ifExtNDot1DState
ifExtNDot1DState.description: Current Dot1d state of the Port.

ifExtNMode.name: ifExtNMode
ifExtNMode.description: This object indicates if the port is in a Trunk mode or access mode. This object provides default switch port value if ifExtIsMonitoring is true(1).

ifExtNAccessVlanId.name: ifExtNAccessVlanId
ifExtNAccessVlanId.description: The VLAN Id when the port is in Access Mode. This object provides default switch port value if ifExtIsMonitoring is true(1).

ifExtNTrunkNativeVlanId.name: ifExtNTrunkNativeVlanId
ifExtNTrunkNativeVlanId.description: The native VLAN Id of the Port, when the port is in dot1q mode. This object provides default switch port value if ifExtIsMonitoring is true(1).

ifExtNTrunkIsAllowedAll.name: ifExtNTrunkIsAllowedAll
ifExtNTrunkIsAllowedAll.description: When the mode of the port is Trunk, this Object indicates if the port is part of all the configured Vlans. This object provides default switch port value if ifExtIsMonitoring is true(1).

ifExtNTrunkAllowedVlanList.name: ifExtNTrunkAllowedVlanList
ifExtNTrunkAllowedVlanList.description: A string of octets containing one bit per VLAN for a total of 4096 VLANs in the management domain. The most significant bit of the octet string is the lowest value VLAN of 4096 VLANs. By setting the bit(1) we indicate that the vlan is part of the interface. The most significant bit of the bitmap is transmitted first. Note that if the length of this string is less than 512 octets, any 'missing' octets are assumed to contain the value zero. This object provides default switch port value if ifExtIsMonitoring is true(1).

ifExtNIngressACLName.name: ifExtNIngressACLName
ifExtNIngressACLName.description: This object represents the Ingress ACL name applied to the port. An Empty string indicates that there is not ACL applied on this port.

ifExtNEgressACLName.name: ifExtNEgressACLName
ifExtNEgressACLName.description: This object represents the Egress ACL name applied to the port. An Empty string indicates that there is not ACL applied on this port.

ifExtNSessionACLName.name: ifExtNSessionACLName
ifExtNSessionACLName.description: This object represents the Session ACL name applied to the port. An Empty string indicates that there is not ACL applied on this port.

ifExtNXsecVlan.name: ifExtNXsecVlan
ifExtNXsecVlan.description: This object indicates if the port is an Xsec Port.

ifExtNIsMonitoring.name: ifExtNIsMonitoring
ifExtNIsMonitoring.description: This object indicates if the port is used for Port monitoring. When the value of this object is true(1), then below objects provide default switch port values configured on this port. ifExtNMode, ifExtNAccessVlanId, ifExtNTrunkNativeVlanId, ifExtNTrunkIsAllowedAll, ifExtNTrunkAllowedVlanList

ifExtNIsMux.name: ifExtNIsMux
ifExtNIsMux.description: This object indicates if the port is used as a MUX Port.
